    12	  Well another typical day in the modem world.	Doesn't it just make you want to
    13	throwup all over the keyboard?	Recently I thought I would call the numbers on
    14	the Megaterm 3.0 Famous Systems phone book.  I thought that these would be the
    15	"Top of the line" BBS's.  As the Mega- term began to dial with Safehouse I
    16	kicked back and watched.  Busy.  Not suprising.  It then proceeded to dial other
    17	BBS's, most of which I never have heard of.  After about two more tries the
    18	program started to freeze.  Not sure what was going on I picked up the phone
    19	only to hear the recording "We're sorry but the number you have dialed has been
    20	disconnected or is no longer in service...".  I then hit [U] to unmark the
    21	number and continue the Megaterm dialing.  Not too worried that that board was
    22	down the Megaterm continued to dail as I again kicked back and watched.  The
    23	very next number that was opening message and the prompt for my password or
    24	'NEW'.  Being a new user I typed 'NEW'.  To my displeasement the system told me
    25	it was a private BBS that allowed no new users and hung me up.	Very displeased
    26	I kicked back in my chair and started to listen a little closer to the TV in the
    27	other room as the Megaterm began to start dialing again.  After two more welcome
    28	busy signals the Megaterm started to flip from 'Click' to 'Busy' and back and
    29	forth.	Confused, I picked up the phone and again heard that dreadfull recording
    30	"Were sorry...".  Very uneasy I pressed [U] to unmark the number.  After a small
    31	welcome string of busy signals I got a ring.  The phone was answered and a
    32	carrier was sent.  The Megaterm then connected for me only to find that it was a
    33	Pixboard.  Very pleased (I love pixboards!) I called back and loaded up Pixterm.
    34	Once conne- cted, pleased to see some nice graphics in the opening message I
    35	then typed in 'NEW'.  Only to find out that a $10 validation fee was required to
    36	access ANYTHING but the main menu and [M]ess- age to SysOp.  After messing
    37	around for a few minutes I got bored and typed "OFF" to leave the system.  I
    38	then returned to Megaterm and it continued to dial.  After another busy signal
    39	the numbers sequence started over.  And I got a ring, before I knew it,the
    40	words:
    41	
    42	   THE SAFEHOUSE MEGANET - PORT #02
    43	    "WHERE YOU'RE ALWAYS WELCOME!"
    44	
    45	  were printed across the screen, me being a regular caller to the board entered
    46	my name and password only then to be logged off due to the fact the that port
    47	was being reserved for a level 5 user.	Very discouraged and then realizing that
    48	some day, The Safehouse would die too such as others favorate systems like
    49	Sherwood Forest II, The Outpost, The World of Cryton, and Sherwood Forest ///.
    50	I then quitely went to bed.
