   107	  After a month or so, with the same old BBS abuse and programming, I took a
   108	look at all the work I had done.  Over 200 files in the [L]ibrary so far, many
   109	new features which have never appeared on a board in the U.S.  (to my known-
   110	ledge) have been thought up, organized, and programmed.  I then thought, when I
   111	take the board over I will be the victim all this major abuse on these other
   112	boards.  What an honor.  God, what an honor!  I then began to wonder, why, why
   113	does everyone abuse everyone else so much?  Are they insecure?	Are they really
   114	that upset?  Are they just blow- ing off a little steam?  Do they enjoy making
   115	enemies?  Do they feel superior to insult others?  I don't know.  I really don't
   116	know.  I myself like to make friends.  Not only just friends that I will talk to
   117	on the phone, but ones that come over on weekeneds, go out partying on Friday
   118	nights, play sports, and just about anything else a true friend does.  Without
   119	knowing that I went to the same school as Shadow's Pawn for almost a year I meet
   120	him at the SysOps house and am now good friends with him.  Despite the fact that
   121	I am two years older then him, he is on the football team, I am in band and
   122	enjoy playing the trumpet, and we had almost no common interests became good
   123	friends because of similar intrests, the computer.  But I still came back to the
   124	same question "Why do they abuse?" Why?  Life is bad enough as it is, and then
   125	there are the feds who are after all us pirates, phreakers, and hackers.  Who
   126	needs more enemies?  While we can all be helping each other the "good old"
   127	traditional computer activi- ties like helping others get up to date "wares",
   128	even if they have a Networker modem and not that "excepted" Apple- cat?  I
   129	remember back when I first got my modem.  I couldn't remember one abuse board.
   130	Not one.  Then suddenly one by one, slowly but surely, they started comming up
   131	with the demand of them due to the large amount of hartred from two users.  Now,
   132	the abuse board is just as common as the public board.	Why?  Why?  Then
   133	somewhere, some one person had an grand idea.  The same thing that happen- ed
   134	over two hundered years ago.  This genious said, that order in the modem society
   135	is a must and some form of goverment must be formed.  Thus came Tele-Trial, with
   136	this new concept came new constitutions, new sub-boards, and an increasement of
   137	tele-conferencing phreaking.  The constitutions would set the laws of the BBS.
   138	The sub-boards would provide a special meeting place for matters of the
   139	tele-trial and the tele-conference for the often called "court room" for the
   140	trial of the def- endent.  This system worked in many places.  Punishments were
   141	often deletion from that board or even to the great extent of credit card
   142	infomation being released, and abused.	But for many, deleting ones password
   143	would not keep them off the system.  They would just call back with a new handle
   144	and abuse more people till he was deleted again.  And the process goes on and
   145	on.  Believe me, I have seen it happen.  So I came to the conclusion that this
   146	method is not full proof.  I then came apon a crazy idea of mine.  Not so sure
   147	of myself I begin my think more indepth.  One hope for me remained, and I then
   148	walked to my computer, put in Apple Writer and began to type.  Now, I have
   149	completed my work.  My task is finished at this moment of Sunday May 26 1985 at
   150	12:55 in the morning.  I thank you for you time and am sorry for any and all
   151	errors.
